WEBVTT

00:01.127 --> 00:03.337
NARRATOR: Previously on Prison Break:
MAHONE: Let me get this straight.

00:03.504 --> 00:07.049
Brothers come to a city that's 15 miles
from the prison they escaped from. Why?

00:07.216 --> 00:10.553
The president's in Chicago to make
a speech, they're up to something.

00:10.720 --> 00:12.722
Legally speaking, this tape is useless.

00:12.889 --> 00:14.974
- So we blackmail her.
- In exchange for what?

00:16.142 --> 00:17.560
A presidential pardon.

00:17.727 --> 00:20.521
MAHONE: We gonna keep crying
about money you've got coming to you?

00:20.688 --> 00:22.648
- Or do you wanna make some more?
- I'm listening.

00:22.815 --> 00:24.025
Ever been to Mexico?

00:24.192 --> 00:26.194
When's the meal coming? I'm starved.

00:27.278 --> 00:29.363
Freshen me up when you get a chance.

00:29.530 --> 00:32.491
Fernando. Fernando.

00:32.658 --> 00:33.701
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

00:33.868 --> 00:36.746
CLAIM MAN: Check this bag for you, sir.
- Oh, no, that's coming with me.

00:37.747 --> 00:41.083
Sir, I know that bag is way over
the weight limit for carryon.

00:41.250 --> 00:42.919
Your bag will be safe.

00:43.085 --> 00:46.547
They're watching you.
But from where? There.

00:46.714 --> 00:49.425
President Reynolds ruined your life,
she ruined my life.

00:49.592 --> 00:50.843
You wanna take the bitch down?

00:51.010 --> 00:53.679
You found your inside man,
but it's gotta be right now.

00:53.846 --> 00:56.182
MAHONE:
Have either of these men checked in?

00:56.349 --> 00:58.267
Yeah. Room 1006.

00:58.434 --> 01:00.895
Later you'll get a package in your
cell. It's from me.

01:01.062 --> 01:03.105
I need you to use it, okay?

01:22.291 --> 01:23.751
Open on 4.

01:29.465 --> 01:31.217
[BUZZES]

01:32.176 --> 01:33.427
I need a hand in here.

01:35.638 --> 01:37.723
[OFFICERS SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

01:39.976 --> 01:43.145
- I need a medic in B-4.
- Let me die.

01:43.312 --> 01:44.647
No.

01:45.856 --> 01:48.818
- Let me die.
OFFICER: Save your breath.

01:49.151 --> 01:51.237
[FRANKLIN GRUNTING]

01:53.072 --> 01:54.949
WOMAN <i>[ON RADIO]:
A large crowd is gathering...</i>

01:55.116 --> 01:57.493
<i>...along Wabash Avenue
here in downtown Chicago.</i>

01:57.660 --> 02:00.830
<i>They're anticipating the arrival
of President Caroline Reynolds...</i>

02:00.997 --> 02:04.667
<i>...who continues her tour with an
appearance at the Grand Carlisle Hotel.</i>

02:06.752 --> 02:08.795
MAN <i>[OVER RADIO]: Inner Ciro/e
approaching the south per/meter.</i>

02:08.963 --> 02:10.256
<i>Mark One.</i>

02:12.300 --> 02:13.968
<i>Marker Two.</i>

02:16.554 --> 02:17.680
<i>Marker Three.</i>

02:22.101 --> 02:23.352
okay-

02:27.523 --> 02:29.150
I think you better go.

02:29.317 --> 02:31.444
- You sure?
- Yeah.

02:31.610 --> 02:34.363
Thank you for your help.
There's nothing more you can do for us.

02:34.530 --> 02:35.698
Doesn't feel right.

02:35.865 --> 02:38.200
I don't think you want any part of this.
Thank you.

02:42.830 --> 02:45.124
- It's 1O minutes away, right?
- At least.

02:46.917 --> 02:51.047
Listen, this doesn't work,
we're gonna need a way out.

02:51.213 --> 02:53.632
- For good.
- Well, that's on you.

02:57.053 --> 02:59.805
Yeah. What about Derek?

02:59.972 --> 03:02.183
- Derek Sweeney?
LINCOLN: Yeah.

03:02.433 --> 03:04.352
- You think he'll be up for this?
LINCOLN: Yeah.

03:04.894 --> 03:06.312
All right.

03:06.479 --> 03:10.066
This is your neck of the woods.
You wanna meet at the park?

03:10.566 --> 03:14.779
- Uh, how's Third and Racine?
- Third and Racine.

03:14.945 --> 03:18.074
Uh, 3:15, the corner.
I'll be there.

03:19.992 --> 03:21.410
If anything happens...

03:23.245 --> 03:24.330
...I love you both.

04:01.575 --> 04:02.952
MAHONE:
Shh.

04:03.119 --> 04:04.495
Key.

04:08.624 --> 04:10.626
Go, go, go.

05:14.648 --> 05:16.358
[DOOR CLOSES]

05:38.589 --> 05:40.299
[SARA GASPS]

05:44.011 --> 05:45.179
Sit down.

06:21.549 --> 06:23.384
When were they here?
Five, 10 minutes?

06:23.759 --> 06:26.095
- They were never here.
- They were here. I know.

06:26.262 --> 06:27.596
Where did they go?

06:29.598 --> 06:31.767
- I don't know.
- No, you do know.

06:31.934 --> 06:35.187
He decided it was for the best
and I couldn't take this anymore.

06:35.354 --> 06:37.523
- It's over, just like that, huh?
- Yeah.

06:37.690 --> 06:41.569
It's over like you flew to New Mexico on
a dead woman's ID to meet up with him?

06:41.735 --> 06:45.072
Or it's over like when you met up
at the train station in Evansville?

06:45.239 --> 06:49.201
Or maybe like the day today, when you
checked in this hotel here two hours ago.

06:49.368 --> 06:51.620
- Which one?
- I don't care if you believe me or not.

06:51.787 --> 06:54.623
- I'm telling you the truth.
- No call. He's not gonna call you?

06:54.790 --> 06:57.876
Don't lie to me.
You don't wanna do that.

07:30.409 --> 07:32.328
Excuse me, can you tell me
where to find...?

07:34.288 --> 07:36.206
[WOMAN SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

08:07.655 --> 08:10.157
Hey. Hey, hombre.

08:10.324 --> 08:11.492
[MAN SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

08:11.659 --> 08:12.701
Hey-

08:15.454 --> 08:17.039
[BOTH GRUNTING]

08:39.477 --> 08:42.815
[ALARM BUZZING]
[PEOPLE SHOUTING]

08:44.066 --> 08:46.360
<i>FRANKLIN:
Hey, I need the phone.</i>

08:46.527 --> 08:48.278
Listen to me, man.
It needs to be today.

08:48.487 --> 08:51.407
My family is in trouble, all right?
There's a man out there...

08:51.573 --> 08:53.534
-...trying to hurt my--
- Your family's fine.

08:53.701 --> 08:56.704
- There's nobody after your family.
- Look at me, man.

08:56.870 --> 08:58.664
Look, I'm not crazy, okay?

09:00.207 --> 09:02.418
I know the rules.

09:03.752 --> 09:07.131
I wouldn't be asking you
if it wasn't an emergency.

09:07.589 --> 09:11.051
Please, just let me use that phone.

09:11.969 --> 09:13.220
Please.

09:18.934 --> 09:20.894
[PHONE RINGING]

09:21.603 --> 09:23.230
- Agent Lang.
FRANKLIN: <i>Yeah, yeah.</i>

09:23.397 --> 09:25.899
<i>I-- I need to speak to Mahone, please.</i>

09:26.275 --> 09:29.820
- Can I have him return?
- Listen, this is Benjamin Miles Franklin.

09:29.987 --> 09:32.448
And I need to speak to Mahone
right away.

09:34.450 --> 09:37.119
- It's Franklin for Mahone.
<i>- I'll</i> take it.

09:40.456 --> 09:43.417
This is Agent Wheeler.
I don't believe we've met before.

09:43.584 --> 09:46.044
I need to speak to Mahone.

09:47.129 --> 09:48.881
Something I can help you with?

09:50.799 --> 09:52.259
Listen...

09:52.676 --> 09:54.762
...I wanna leave a message for him.

09:55.053 --> 09:56.430
<i>You tell him.</i>

09:57.848 --> 10:00.642
You tell him that I'll do what he wants
me to do, okay?

10:00.809 --> 10:04.104
I just need a little bit more time.
I'll do it.

10:04.271 --> 10:06.273
Just don't hurt them.

10:06.607 --> 10:09.943
You hear me?
Don't hurt them.

10:13.906 --> 10:15.157
What's up?

10:16.950 --> 10:18.160
Excuse me.

10:48.190 --> 10:49.858
[DEREK GASPING]

10:50.025 --> 10:54.196
- Are you crazy? What are you doing here?
- Keep your voice down. Keep it down.

11:00.035 --> 11:03.080
How you been? You all right?

11:03.247 --> 11:05.374
- It's good to see you, man.
- You too, brother.

11:05.541 --> 11:08.377
If the guys knew you were here,
they might not be cool about it.

11:08.544 --> 11:10.838
I ain't hanging around, man.
I need a favor.

11:11.004 --> 11:14.007
- You owe me.
- I do. You know I do.

11:14.550 --> 11:15.717
Look, it's...

11:17.177 --> 11:20.806
Look, it's just your situation right now.
I mean, I just had a kid, a baby boy...

11:20.973 --> 11:24.184
-...and I-- I promised Maria--
- I didn't come here to cause trouble.

11:24.351 --> 11:26.562
I'm short on friends.
I need you to hook me up.

11:27.187 --> 11:29.898
You're the only one who can do it
without the green up front.

11:30.065 --> 11:33.652
I'm serious about this, man.
Here. I need it.

11:42.244 --> 11:44.746
Okay. I'll give it a shot.

11:44.913 --> 11:46.665
- By when?
- ASAP.

11:46.790 --> 11:48.750
- Tomorrow? The next day?
- Now.

11:53.255 --> 11:54.673
Now.

11:58.927 --> 12:02.139
All right, Linc. Come with me.

12:04.516 --> 12:06.602
[SIRENS WAILING]

12:20.532 --> 12:22.618
[CROWD CHEERING]

12:35.589 --> 12:37.299
AGENT 1 [OVER <i>RADIO]:
Stand by. Marker six.</i>

12:38.717 --> 12:40.802
<i>Escort team, stand by.</i>

12:44.848 --> 12:46.058
<i>Okay, stand by for exit.</i>

12:54.274 --> 12:55.943
<i>Seven clear.</i>

12:58.737 --> 12:59.905
<i>Approaching hotel entrance.</i>

13:00.072 --> 13:02.824
<i>Everything looks clear.</i>

13:09.289 --> 13:11.375
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

13:17.172 --> 13:19.675
AGENT <i>2: He's</i> over <i>the line. Got him.</i>
AGENT 1: <i>Take h/m. Take him down.</i>

13:19.841 --> 13:22.135
AGENT 3: <i>Gel' some hands on that guy.</i>
AGENT 2: <i>Hold if still.</i>

13:22.302 --> 13:24.805
AGENT 1: <i>Dela/n h/m. Defa/n h/m.</i>
AGENT 3: <i>Get him on ground.</i>

13:24.972 --> 13:26.598
AGENT 1:
<i>Talk to that guy.</i>

14:04.386 --> 14:06.054
Who saw him go down?
Any press?

14:06.221 --> 14:08.598
We got him down pretty quick
but you never know.

14:08.807 --> 14:11.601
- Somebody may have gotten a shot.
- Check around.

14:12.102 --> 14:14.229
Confiscate cameras if you need to.

14:14.396 --> 14:16.898
Put out a statement
before rumors get started.

14:17.899 --> 14:19.818
And get everyone out of here.

14:19.943 --> 14:20.986
Now.

14:21.153 --> 14:23.071
We're still waiting
for the response from--

14:25.991 --> 14:28.201
[WHISPERING]
You and I both know that this situation...

14:28.368 --> 14:30.454
...requires us to abandon protocol.

14:31.455 --> 14:34.833
I don't know what you need to tell them,
but I need your men to leave.

14:36.293 --> 14:37.836
Now.

14:39.838 --> 14:41.465
Yes, sir.

14:47.929 --> 14:49.264
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Where's your brother?

14:49.431 --> 14:51.224
- I need to see the president.
KIM: Really?

14:52.142 --> 14:54.061
And you think that's a possibility?

14:54.227 --> 14:58.023
- She'll want to hear what I have to say.
- Oh, I highly doubt that.

15:04.362 --> 15:07.324
The only person you get to talk to...

15:07.991 --> 15:09.618
...is me.

15:10.452 --> 15:13.663
And the only way you're gonna live
through the next hour...

15:13.872 --> 15:15.957
...is if you tell me where to find
your brother.

15:17.334 --> 15:18.752
Okay-

15:21.213 --> 15:24.174
- He's in a safe place.
- Be more specific.

15:25.050 --> 15:26.968
Specifically...

15:27.761 --> 15:30.347
...a place you will never find him.

15:42.192 --> 15:44.111
I had the honor...

15:45.779 --> 15:47.948
...to attend Mountbrook
Military Academy...

15:52.828 --> 15:54.830
...whose mission it is...

15:54.996 --> 15:58.291
...to ensure the greatness of this country,
its future leadership...

15:58.458 --> 16:00.210
...encouraging patriotism...

16:00.544 --> 16:04.047
...building a strong moral foundation
and providing the service of men...

16:04.965 --> 16:10.220
...committed to the values of honor,
freedom and country.

16:11.096 --> 16:14.224
But, first and foremost...

16:14.391 --> 16:16.476
...they taught you this.

16:16.643 --> 16:18.562
[MICHAEL GRUNTING]

16:27.028 --> 16:28.989
[MICHAEL COUGHING]

16:34.619 --> 16:37.038
MARICRUZ:
How do you say "cherries" again?

16:37.247 --> 16:38.707
<i>Cereza.</i>

16:39.457 --> 16:42.043
Looks like you have
to get more cerezas.

16:42.210 --> 16:44.087
Mami, I got you a hundred pistachios.

16:44.254 --> 16:48.508
- With the right amount of salt too.
- Well, it's a combination. I need both.

16:48.884 --> 16:51.261
Why am I sucker for you, huh?

16:51.469 --> 16:53.555
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

16:58.977 --> 17:02.105
[WOMAN ON TV
SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

17:07.611 --> 17:09.695
[SUCRE SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

17:09.863 --> 17:12.991
MARICRUZ: What? What's she saying?
SUCRE: That looks like T-Bag.

17:13.116 --> 17:14.742
MARICRUZ: What?
- Shh.

17:14.992 --> 17:18.079
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

17:19.830 --> 17:22.291
He said he was trying to steal luggage
from the airport.

17:24.461 --> 17:26.922
He's got five million dollars.
Why would he--?

17:34.512 --> 17:36.598
Unless he doesn't have it.

17:37.807 --> 17:39.142
Unless he lost it there.

17:39.309 --> 17:41.686
- Stop it, Fernando.
- What?

17:41.853 --> 17:44.940
Do you really believe that that money
is at the airport?

17:45.649 --> 17:49.945
Hey, forget it.
Look at what we have together.

17:50.111 --> 17:52.155
Do you really wanna risk that?

17:52.656 --> 17:55.492
We have everything that we need.

17:55.909 --> 17:58.036
- Except your cerezas.
- Right.

18:01.122 --> 18:02.582
I'll be right back.

18:02.832 --> 18:04.334
Fernando.

18:16.805 --> 18:20.392
Baby. I'll be right back.

18:53.717 --> 18:57.220
You gotta know it's not real hard
for me to recognize a junkie.

18:57.721 --> 19:02.100
L-- I-- I'm saying you don't look so good.

19:05.520 --> 19:07.022
I'm fine.

19:09.691 --> 19:11.693
You mind me asking what you're taking?

19:13.653 --> 19:16.114
- Here, you want one?
- No, that's okay.

19:18.575 --> 19:20.327
Save it for later.

19:24.164 --> 19:25.790
Varatril.

19:28.126 --> 19:31.296
Benzodiazepine's a
hard-core tranquilizer, man.

19:31.463 --> 19:33.298
Take these every day?

19:34.424 --> 19:36.384
Twenty milligrams.

19:38.261 --> 19:41.181
You must feel like you're walking
underwater.

19:42.432 --> 19:43.850
I do.

19:44.809 --> 19:46.853
It's very quiet down here.

19:47.604 --> 19:50.523
That's why you started, right?
The peace and quiet?

19:51.232 --> 19:53.651
That's not why you do it anymore
though, is it?

19:56.154 --> 19:59.366
Now it's the headaches, right?
And you probably don't sleep.

20:01.618 --> 20:04.371
And you know you're gonna
destroy yourself, right?

20:07.082 --> 20:09.793
I haven't ruled that out as a possibility.

20:12.754 --> 20:14.964
Hope we hear from your boyfriend.

20:15.173 --> 20:17.217
[MICHAEL COUGHING]

20:19.469 --> 20:21.805
There's one difference between
me and Agent Mahone.

20:22.722 --> 20:26.851
He doesn't know the value of a bird in the
hand. He keeps beating around that bush.

20:27.018 --> 20:29.687
But if you don't give up Burrows,
I don't care.

20:33.650 --> 20:34.818
One down, one to go.

20:34.984 --> 20:37.445
REYNOLDS:
I need to talk to Mr. Scofield.

20:37.821 --> 20:38.905
Alone.

21:13.857 --> 21:15.567
Madam President.

21:16.359 --> 21:17.861
Could I...

21:19.320 --> 21:21.072
...have a word?

21:22.657 --> 21:25.618
It wouldn't be prudent for me
to leave you alone with Mr. Scof--

21:25.785 --> 21:29.497
My men are right outside this door.
I have a right to privacy.

21:29.664 --> 21:31.833
Your rights...

21:32.000 --> 21:33.251
...aren't my first concern.

21:33.376 --> 21:36.463
Do I need to remind you
who you are talking to?

21:36.629 --> 21:41.009
Step outside and close the door
behind you.

21:43.303 --> 21:44.971
[KIM CLEARS THROAT]

22:05.325 --> 22:08.703
The things you do for your brother.

22:09.078 --> 22:10.872
It's impressive.

22:11.206 --> 22:13.666
I could say the same for you.

22:16.044 --> 22:17.587
- But I won't.
- Bear in mind...

22:17.754 --> 22:20.673
...your opinion means little to me.

22:21.174 --> 22:23.009
This tape.

22:23.468 --> 22:25.720
You have it with you?

22:26.346 --> 22:27.805
No.

22:29.057 --> 22:31.893
But I can arrange for you to hear it.

22:32.060 --> 22:33.436
[CHUCKLING]

22:33.603 --> 22:37.941
You don't make arrangements for me,
Mr. Scofield.

22:38.107 --> 22:40.527
I have people for that.

22:41.110 --> 22:45.114
I'm not exactly sure
what is on this tape...

22:45.323 --> 22:48.117
...but I doubt it's of any interest to me.

22:48.326 --> 22:51.454
It's a recorded conversation
between you and your brother.

22:51.621 --> 22:56.251
Well, out of millions of conversations that
I had with my brother during his lifetime--

22:56.417 --> 22:58.378
I'll narrow it down for you.

22:58.878 --> 23:02.966
It was recorded sometime
after his death.

23:04.759 --> 23:06.094
And this...

23:06.844 --> 23:09.681
...particular conversation...

23:11.724 --> 23:14.227
...you might wanna keep in the family.

23:17.272 --> 23:19.148
And where is it?

23:19.357 --> 23:22.860
Twenty different copies
in 2O different locations.

23:23.278 --> 23:25.738
I can call my brother right now.

23:25.905 --> 23:27.615
He can play it for you.

23:27.782 --> 23:30.910
Not on the phone.
Have him bring it here.

23:32.245 --> 23:33.913
These are the terms.

23:35.373 --> 23:38.001
You can hear it over the phone...

23:38.459 --> 23:41.087
...or you can hear it on the news.

23:42.463 --> 23:44.173
It's up to you.

23:48.469 --> 23:50.430
You know, it's why I started.

23:51.055 --> 23:52.682
Started what?

23:53.141 --> 23:55.393
Using. Same reason as you.

23:55.518 --> 23:58.396
Why? Because you had to stay up
all night during residency?

23:58.563 --> 24:00.106
[MAHONE CHUCKLING]

24:00.273 --> 24:03.401
Because the bass player dumped you
in front of the whole sorority?

24:03.526 --> 24:05.653
Yeah, you and I got a lot in common.

24:06.571 --> 24:08.489
I've seen people die too.

24:09.490 --> 24:12.243
I'm assuming you didn't make them die.

24:13.036 --> 24:14.704
SARA:
You need help.

24:15.288 --> 24:17.457
Not what I'm looking for.

24:23.046 --> 24:25.632
For your sake, I hope your boyfriend
calls back real soon.

24:49.447 --> 24:51.157
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

24:54.994 --> 24:56.788
Maricruz?

25:01.125 --> 25:02.960
Where the hell's everybody?

25:06.589 --> 25:08.091
Mami?

25:11.761 --> 25:14.639
Hey, lookie here. Good old Sucre.

25:14.806 --> 25:16.766
What'd you do?
Where are they? Maricruz.

25:16.933 --> 25:19.602
Hey, hey, hey.
Keep your cap on.

25:19.769 --> 25:21.771
Out picking apples
for the Snuffaluffagus.

25:22.230 --> 25:23.606
- If you ever--
- Calm down.

25:23.773 --> 25:26.401
They're gonna walk back in here
any minute.

25:26.651 --> 25:28.486
Which means trouble.

25:28.945 --> 25:34.283
Unless you wanna see me try out the new
T-20-Z on your <i>bel/a</i> muchacha Mari-poon.

25:35.952 --> 25:38.121
I think you better come with me.

25:38.871 --> 25:40.540
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

25:44.502 --> 25:45.837
Yeah?

25:46.212 --> 25:48.423
<i>REYNOLDS".
Lincoln Burrows?</i>

25:49.006 --> 25:50.425
Caroline Reynolds.

25:51.426 --> 25:55.221
I understand you have
something for me.

25:59.767 --> 26:02.145
- You still there?
- Oh, I'm <i>here.</i>

26:02.645 --> 26:05.022
It's good to finally talk to you.

26:05.523 --> 26:09.819
Wish I had the chance one of those
242 nights I spent on death row, you--

26:09.986 --> 26:12.989
Please, just play the tape.

26:22.039 --> 26:24.667
REYNOLDS [ON RECORDING]:
lfis' awful, / <i>know.</i>

26:24.834 --> 26:29.172
<i>But the choice was clear. You needed
to be far away from all of this.</i>

26:29.338 --> 26:32.842
<i>TERRENCE [ON RECORDING]: lam.
I'm the ls/e of Terrence, far off to sea.</i>

26:33.009 --> 26:35.553
<i>REYNOLDS".
But I'm still here for you.</i>

26:35.678 --> 26:38.890
<i>Now, listen to me.
Don't dwell on the negative.</i>

26:39.056 --> 26:41.142
Some people
deserve to dwell, Caroline.

26:41.309 --> 26:44.270
You know I'm only a phone call away.

26:44.437 --> 26:48.149
Mm-hm. And three thousand miles.

26:51.569 --> 26:54.238
Do you know how cold it is here?

26:54.405 --> 26:56.657
<i>REYNOLDS [ON RECORDING]:
We talked about this, Terrence.</i>

26:56.824 --> 26:59.911
<i>You knew that you would be lonely,
but it's only temporary.</i>

27:00.077 --> 27:02.455
<i>His appeals process has started already.</i>

27:02.622 --> 27:05.583
<i>This is gonna fly by quicker
than your 20s.</i>

27:05.708 --> 27:09.337
<i>And soon the world will forget
all about him...</i>

27:09.504 --> 27:12.465
...and they'll forget about you too.
I promise.

27:12.632 --> 27:14.091
But...

27:15.343 --> 27:19.013
...it's killing me not being able
to see you...

27:19.180 --> 27:22.099
-...sweet Caroline.
- I wanna see you too.

27:22.266 --> 27:26.020
<i>- Buz' that can '1' happen r/ghz' now.</i>
- This <i>house is so</i> big.

27:26.187 --> 27:28.731
I just-- I just think of you...

27:29.857 --> 27:31.734
...lying in bed.

27:32.235 --> 27:35.404
- I know. Me too.
- Your warmth, your touch.

27:45.081 --> 27:46.290
REYNOLDS:
Was it quick...

27:47.917 --> 27:49.877
...when he killed himself?

27:50.962 --> 27:53.422
Well, it was a lot quicker
than how my father died.

27:53.631 --> 27:55.550
They shot him in the back.

27:56.843 --> 27:58.719
He died in my arms.

27:59.804 --> 28:01.764
I just wanna know what happened.

28:03.808 --> 28:06.352
Your brother apologized.

28:07.812 --> 28:12.149
He said he was sorry and then he blew
his brains out all over the wall.

28:14.485 --> 28:16.153
It was quick...

28:16.320 --> 28:18.239
...and it was his decision.

28:19.365 --> 28:21.576
And now it's time
for you to make yours.

28:27.039 --> 28:28.833
[CHUCKLING]

28:29.000 --> 28:33.004
No, no, no, no. Man, you know,
I-- I can't-- I can't do it. I can't do that.

28:33.880 --> 28:35.506
Yes, you can.

28:36.132 --> 28:38.426
There's nothing to be afraid of.

28:38.843 --> 28:40.344
You don't get it, do you?

28:41.137 --> 28:43.431
You can't stop this guy.

28:43.598 --> 28:47.351
Not without your cooperation, I can't.
But if you talk to me...

28:48.352 --> 28:51.439
...if you tell me what's going on,
I can take care of you, okay?

28:51.606 --> 28:53.691
You've gotta trust me, Mr. Franklin.

28:54.317 --> 28:56.277
I can help you.

28:58.863 --> 29:00.114
C-Note, right?

29:01.365 --> 29:03.200
Yeah, whatever.

29:08.748 --> 29:12.710
All I need you to do is tell me exactly
what Agent Mahone told you.

29:14.629 --> 29:18.174
If you give me Mahone,
I'll give you your life back.

29:18.883 --> 29:21.594
BELLICK: God's been smiling
down on me, I can tell you that.

29:21.761 --> 29:23.721
First I caught up to Haywire
up in Algoma.

29:23.888 --> 29:26.724
He did a dive off an elevator
before they could put him away...

29:26.891 --> 29:29.477
-...but I still get the reward.
- Wait, wait. He's dead?

29:29.644 --> 29:32.980
Yep. Like a gnat on a Peterbilt. Hope you
don't take the same route, Sucre.

29:33.147 --> 29:36.776
- Hell, no. I got plenty reasons to live.
- I hope a few of them are in Fox River.

29:36.943 --> 29:40.196
Or maybe if you play nice, I'll throw
your Maricruz a couple of bills.

29:40.363 --> 29:42.823
- After I turn you in.
- How much are you getting for us?

29:42.990 --> 29:46.744
A hundred grand. I bet you never thought
your ass would be worth all that.

29:46.911 --> 29:48.746
Wait, wait, wait.

29:49.413 --> 29:52.875
What if I know where you can
get 5 million dollars?

29:56.128 --> 29:58.047
You heard me.

29:58.881 --> 30:02.218
- Where is it?
- I could take you there...

30:02.510 --> 30:06.138
...if you didn't have to take me back
to the States and turn me back in.

30:06.931 --> 30:08.641
Where is it?

30:11.310 --> 30:13.270
SUCRE:
T-Bag's in town.

30:13.980 --> 30:17.358
REYNOLDS:
I made my commitment a long time ago.

30:18.067 --> 30:21.320
I agreed to put my country
ahead of myself...

30:21.487 --> 30:23.864
...like a mother does for a child.

30:26.367 --> 30:28.285
And I thought...

30:28.911 --> 30:32.957
...that what I was doing was noble
and that I would be rewarded.

30:33.124 --> 30:34.291
You were wrong.

30:34.458 --> 30:38.629
Don't you see
that I'm a pawn in this too?

30:39.338 --> 30:42.133
The power that has taken over
this country...

30:42.299 --> 30:46.053
...is like a cancer
and it will stop at nothing.

30:46.303 --> 30:50.141
- It is out of my control.
- So is this.

30:50.641 --> 30:53.227
Tell me what you want from me.

30:54.520 --> 30:56.105
Uncuff me.

30:56.564 --> 30:58.649
- I don't have the keys.
- You'll get them.

30:58.816 --> 31:01.986
Second, I want you to arrange for me
to walk away from here alone.

31:02.153 --> 31:03.821
No surveillance.

31:05.406 --> 31:06.490
Okay-

31:07.408 --> 31:09.285
And finally...

31:10.327 --> 31:14.832
...I want a presidential pardon for me
and my brother...

31:14.999 --> 31:18.169
...fully exonerating us
of all our crimes.

31:18.335 --> 31:20.421
And I want it today.

31:29.930 --> 31:33.851
REYNOLDS: I can't just hand out
pardons to anyone I choose.

31:34.018 --> 31:37.730
- There is a process, rules.
- This is no exception.

31:37.897 --> 31:41.358
A document will be delivered for
your approval just like any pardon.

31:41.525 --> 31:43.235
You'll sign it and then file it...

31:43.402 --> 31:46.489
...with the attorney general,
who'll submit it to Presidential Record.

31:46.655 --> 31:49.909
Fine. I will sign whatever
you need me to sign.

31:50.076 --> 31:52.745
That's very kind.
But we both know that's not enough.

31:52.912 --> 31:55.039
What do you want from me?

31:55.206 --> 31:58.375
I will unlock you myself,
walk you out of here.

31:58.542 --> 32:00.961
What, you want me to drive you
to the airport?

32:01.128 --> 32:04.381
I guess I'm not as trusting as I used to be.
Especially with paperwork.

32:04.548 --> 32:06.509
It's so easy to lose.

32:06.675 --> 32:09.470
Now, I want you to go out there
in front of everyone...

32:09.637 --> 32:12.973
...and announce our full pardon
on live TV.

32:14.391 --> 32:16.143
You're insane.

32:16.310 --> 32:18.646
That is not the way things are done.

32:18.813 --> 32:21.315
This is not a vacuum.
People will ask questions.

32:21.482 --> 32:24.902
Pardon. On stage. Now.

32:28.906 --> 32:34.411
And how do I know that you won't
release the tape an hour later?

32:35.830 --> 32:37.248
You don't.

32:38.040 --> 32:40.084
You'll just have to take my word for it.

32:41.627 --> 32:45.297
- Well, I need more than that.
- Well, you're not gonna get it.

32:49.593 --> 32:51.095
Caroline...

32:52.179 --> 32:53.848
...it's time.

32:54.557 --> 32:56.475
Make your choice.

33:02.606 --> 33:08.445
Adams, I need you to uncuff the detainee
and bring him here to be released.

33:08.988 --> 33:11.740
[WHISPERING]
What are you doing?

33:11.949 --> 33:16.120
I am going to make an announcement
pardoning Mr. Scofield and his brother...

33:16.287 --> 33:19.039
...and he will walk away unharmed.

33:19.206 --> 33:20.291
Are you out of your mind?

33:21.292 --> 33:24.879
He has brought some indisputable
evidence to light.

33:25.045 --> 33:28.299
We could end this all, right now.

33:28.465 --> 33:29.800
You're gonna let them walk?

33:29.967 --> 33:34.305
I am the commander in chief,
and you are a corporate lackey.

33:34.722 --> 33:37.808
I am making the calls now.
You have no authority.

33:39.685 --> 33:41.979
My men will see to it...

33:42.146 --> 33:45.691
...that Mr. Scofield walks away
without the interference...

33:45.858 --> 33:48.986
...of you and your pit bulls.

34:15.429 --> 34:17.056
[KNOCKS]

34:22.853 --> 34:25.188
- You alone?
DEREK: Yeah.

34:27.065 --> 34:30.194
- How'd you do?
- Three tickets, one cabin, one way.

34:30.360 --> 34:31.820
Nice.

34:32.196 --> 34:35.032
- I owe you.
- No. We're even.

34:35.199 --> 34:36.824
- These are for you.
- Nice.

34:37.326 --> 34:38.702
And this.

34:41.871 --> 34:44.123
- What's this?
- Eddie. When you broke out...

34:44.291 --> 34:46.710
...he bet me a hundred bucks
you'd be caught in a week.

34:46.877 --> 34:48.920
I said, no way. Not the Linc I know.

34:49.088 --> 34:51.172
Figured I'd split it with you.

34:53.467 --> 34:54.885
So this is it, huh?

34:55.552 --> 34:56.929
Yeah.

34:58.264 --> 34:59.682
Good luck.

35:02.059 --> 35:04.353
- You take care. All right.
- You too.

35:05.062 --> 35:06.605
You be safe.

35:30.587 --> 35:33.424
- This is your neck of the woods.
- Yeah. How's Third and Racine?

35:33.590 --> 35:35.301
I'll be there.

35:42.933 --> 35:45.102
I don't wanna do this. I really don't.

35:46.270 --> 35:47.980
What are you talking about?

35:48.147 --> 35:50.316
You can't say that I didn't give
you a choice...

35:50.482 --> 35:52.401
...you never
take the easy way. You--

35:52.776 --> 35:55.279
And I noticed that about you. You--

35:55.446 --> 35:59.241
I should never expect it to be any
different but I have a job to do...

35:59.408 --> 36:01.201
...a job that I'm being made to do.

36:01.368 --> 36:03.245
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

36:05.122 --> 36:06.165
Pick it up, Sara.

36:07.708 --> 36:08.876
Sara, pick it up.

36:09.960 --> 36:12.629
- Pick up.
SARA: Wait, wait.

36:14.673 --> 36:16.216
Don't move.

36:16.383 --> 36:19.636
Just don't-- Don't move.

36:20.888 --> 36:22.931
Okay, I need the phone.
Give me the phone.

36:24.308 --> 36:26.393
Stay right where you are, please.

36:28.479 --> 36:29.897
You don't really wanna do this.

36:30.064 --> 36:32.399
You don't know the first thing about
what I want.

36:47.664 --> 36:49.166
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

36:50.626 --> 36:52.669
- You got my message?
LANG: <i>Yeah.</i>

36:56.006 --> 36:57.925
- I got her.
- She's on her way out.

36:58.884 --> 37:01.970
<i>Follow her. She'll take you
right to Scofield.</i>

37:22.658 --> 37:24.034
Sir...

37:24.743 --> 37:26.537
...we need to talk.

37:29.081 --> 37:31.500
In just a few minutes, the president...

37:31.667 --> 37:35.379
...is going to announce a pardon
for Burrows and Scofield.

37:35.546 --> 37:38.132
As you're well aware,
this is quite a departure.

37:39.049 --> 37:42.719
She's always been willing to play ball
but I think we need to take some action.

37:44.304 --> 37:45.639
Sir...

37:48.058 --> 37:50.352
...I hate to disturb you...

37:50.936 --> 37:55.816
...but I'm not sure you realize the gravity
of what she's about to do.

38:10.998 --> 38:12.749
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

38:14.626 --> 38:17.337
- Michael.
- Sara.

38:17.588 --> 38:20.549
- It worked.
- The pardon?

38:21.383 --> 38:23.760
She's announcing it any minute.

38:24.761 --> 38:27.097
Oh, my God.

38:27.848 --> 38:29.766
Oh, my God. Michael, that's amazing.

38:29.933 --> 38:31.852
<i>MICHAEL:
Jusz' get here, okay?</i>

38:33.270 --> 38:35.439
I'm on, uh...

38:35.939 --> 38:39.276
...Highland. It's a warehouse
that runs right down to the water.

38:39.443 --> 38:41.778
Yeah. Yeah, I'm on my way.

38:57.711 --> 38:59.129
[KNOCKS]

39:14.770 --> 39:16.396
[MICHAEL GRUNTS]

39:20.442 --> 39:23.237
- We did it.
- Yeah?

39:26.657 --> 39:28.116
What happened to your face, man?

39:28.784 --> 39:31.411
If you wanna take the ride...

39:32.120 --> 39:33.789
...you gotta buy the ticket.

39:34.081 --> 39:38.335
Yeah, right. Well, Derek hooked us up
with a cabin on one of those freighters.

39:38.669 --> 39:40.379
South America via the Great Lakes.

39:40.546 --> 39:45.592
Well, we're not gonna need that.
But this is appreciated.

39:45.759 --> 39:47.886
One more time, bro.

39:48.053 --> 39:51.014
- We did it?
- It's done.

39:56.061 --> 39:59.022
Oh, I wish I could've seen the look
on her face.

39:59.773 --> 40:00.941
No, you don't.

40:02.359 --> 40:03.819
Oh, yeah, I do.

40:08.615 --> 40:11.702
- Unbelievable.
- She's gonna do it.

40:13.120 --> 40:14.705
Unbelievable.

40:16.415 --> 40:20.252
<i>The president is now taking the stage
here at the Grand Carlisle Hotel.</i>

40:20.419 --> 40:22.504
<i>The 2-hour delay in her appearance...</i>

40:22.671 --> 40:26.508
...due to an investigation characterized
by Press Secretary Ryan Berg...

40:26.675 --> 40:29.219
...as "an over-zealous fan"...

40:35.183 --> 40:38.437
- You are not going to do this.
- I'm afraid I am.

40:38.604 --> 40:41.898
- Developments you need to be aware of.
- I have made my decision...

40:42.065 --> 40:45.193
...and I would appreciate
you not second-guessing me.

40:45.402 --> 40:48.655
I don't think you understand.
We know your secrets too.

40:50.907 --> 40:52.576
We can reveal them just as easily.

40:53.410 --> 40:56.413
You need to ask yourself who you
fear more. Michael Scofield...

40:57.122 --> 40:58.248
...or us?

40:58.707 --> 41:00.459
- You've got 3O seconds.
- Yeah.

41:00.626 --> 41:02.419
I won't keep you.

41:03.253 --> 41:05.589
- The world is waiting.
MAN 1: Ten seconds.

41:05.756 --> 41:08.634
<i>MAN 2: Ladies and gentlemen,
the President of the United States.</i>

41:08.800 --> 41:14.014
MAN 1:
Nine, eight, seven, six, five...

41:14.181 --> 41:17.934
...four, three, two...

41:19.853 --> 41:24.608
REYNOLDS: Thank you for waiting
so patiently all afternoon.

41:25.025 --> 41:28.570
If it were not for the support
of this great state...

41:28.737 --> 41:30.947
...my home state of Illinois...

41:31.615 --> 41:33.617
[CROWD CHEERING]

41:35.619 --> 41:38.163
...I would not be here today.

41:38.330 --> 41:40.999
Which is why I have chosen today...

41:41.166 --> 41:45.295
...to make
this very important announcement.

41:46.088 --> 41:49.633
A situation has recently come to light...

41:49.800 --> 41:52.678
<i>...and I feel that I must take action.</i>

41:53.136 --> 41:57.349
<i>It is my job as president of this
great country...</i>

41:57.516 --> 42:00.185
<i>...to make rational decisions...</i>

42:00.352 --> 42:02.312
<i>...when I am given facts.</i>

42:03.355 --> 42:08.318
Decisions that are best not for me
but for the people.

42:10.278 --> 42:11.947
And so...

42:12.114 --> 42:15.158
...after much consideration...

42:15.325 --> 42:18.537
<i>...I regret to inform you...</i>

42:18.829 --> 42:24.042
...that I have been diagnosed with
a highly malignant form of cancer.

42:24.209 --> 42:25.877
[CROWD GASPS]

42:28.130 --> 42:30.799
<i>REYNOLDS".
And because of that reason...</i>

42:31.007 --> 42:36.221
...I am no longer fit to serve
as your commander in chief.

42:37.723 --> 42:42.018
In the best interest of this country,
effective immediately...

42:42.936 --> 42:48.233
...I am stepping down
as president of the United States.

42:48.442 --> 42:50.610
[REPORTERS SHOUTING
INDISTINCTLY]

42:52.362 --> 42:55.073
WOMAN <i>[ON TV]: Lad/es and gentlemen,
in a shocking announcement...</i>

42:55.240 --> 42:58.243
If she ain't the president,
the tape's useless.

42:58.535 --> 43:00.704
She can't pardon anyone.

43:01.955 --> 43:03.540
We got nothing.

43:06.251 --> 43:08.295
<i>WOMAN". --she will no longer serve
as the president.</i>

43:08.462 --> 43:10.046
There's only one thing we can do.

43:12.632 --> 43:14.551
We gotta disappear.

43:16.178 --> 43:17.596
Forever.

